    <div class="main-content">
        <h1 class="title">5 Simple Morning Habits to Boost Your Day</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Start your day right with these easy routines for energy and focus.</p>

        <img src="https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2017/08/06/12/03/people-2592070_960_720.jpg" alt="Sunrise view or peaceful morning" class="recipe-image">

        <h2 class="section-title">Habits to Adopt:</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>**Wake up gently:** Avoid hitting snooze. Try waking up 15-30 minutes earlier than usual.</li>
            <li>**Hydrate immediately:** Drink a glass of water before anything else to rehydrate your body.</li>
            <li>**Move your body:** A quick stretch, yoga, or a short walk can energize you.</li>
            <li>**Practice mindfulness:** Spend 5-10 minutes meditating or simply focusing on your breath.</li>
            <li>**Plan your top 3 tasks:** Identify the most important things to achieve for the day to gain clarity.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="section-title">Why These Habits Work:</h2>
        <div class="instructions">
            <p>Implementing a consistent morning routine can profoundly impact your entire day. By starting with intention, you set a positive tone, reduce stress, and improve your productivity. These habits are designed to be simple, making them easy to integrate into even the busiest schedules.</p>
            <p>A well-structured morning routine gives you control over your day, boosts mental clarity, and ensures you approach tasks with a fresh and focused mindset. Experiment with these habits to discover what works best for you!</p>
        </div>

        <img src="https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2017/03/02/16/54/sunrise-2111818_960_720.jpg" alt="Morning coffee and notebook" class="recipe-image">

        <div class="extra-info">
            <h2 class="section-title">The Power of Consistency</h2>
            <p>The real secret to these habits is **consistency**. Even if you miss a day, don't give up! Just pick up where you left off the next morning. Small, consistent efforts compound over time, leading to significant improvements in your well-being.</p>
            <p>Starting your day with purpose can lead to better decision-making, increased energy throughout the afternoon, and an overall greater sense of accomplishment.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

